28/05/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer urged Macedonia to strengthen its judicial system, which he described as a prerequisite for sustainable economic and political development.
Meeting with President Branko Crvenkovski and Prime Minister-designate Hari Kostov on Thursday (27 May), de Hoop Scheffer said that the country should intensify reforms to guarantee full implementation of the Ohrid Peace Accord.
The next stop in his tour is Bosnia and Herzegovina.
In other news Thursday, parliament overwhelmingly approved a government resolution to boost Macedonia's troop presence in Iraq.
A 32-member special operations unit will be deployed from 1 June to 15 December.
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 28/05/04;
A1 TV, Makfax - 27/05/04)
